    {
      "html": "<b>Hon.\nCathy </b><b><a name=\"_Toc40905758\">Cox</a></b><b>�(Minister of Sport, Culture and Heritage):</b> I'm exceptionally\nhonoured to rise in the House today to celebrate Vyshyvanka Day. ",
      "index": "00023",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "����� Vyshyvanka\nDay is an annual celebration where Ukrainian communities all over the world\nwear beautiful shirts adorned with our traditional Ukrainian embroidery, or\nvyshyvankas, as a symbol of unity and our pride in our Ukrainian heritage.",
      "index": "00024",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "����� Vyshyvankas\nare much more than just beautiful garments. They are steeped in our deep\nUkrainian tradition and heritage. Archeological research in Ukraine shows that\nthe very detailed embroidery depicted on vyshyvankas has existed there since\nprehistoric times. They have long been a symbol of hope for a brighter future\nand showcase the incredible creativity of Ukrainian people.",
      "index": "00025",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "����� Canada\nand Manitoba have made Ukrainian ties to Ukraine�have many Ukrainian ties to\nUkraine and its people. Thousands of Ukraines, like my babas and gigis, came to\nour province seeking a hope and a dream for a better life in the late 1800s and\nearly 1900s. These resilient and hard-working individuals built so much of\nManitoba and the very Manitoba that we call home today. They made sacrifices,\nworked hard and ensured that their heritage was deeply rooted in their\ncommunities.",
      "index": "00026",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "����� That\nsense of community and heritage remains strong today, Madam Speaker, and I am\nproud to say that Manitoba is even the home of Canada's National Ukrainian\nFestival, which I can't wait to attend in Dauphin in 2021.",
      "index": "00027",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "����� Today\nin the Chamber there are many members of Ukrainian descent, and I know how\nincredibly proud our ancestors would have been to see so many Ukrainian\nlegislators here in this Chamber.",
      "index": "00028",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "����� Our\ngovernment recognizes the important contributions that Ukrainians have made in\nour province. We are proud to support Vyshyvanka Day, which raises awareness of\nthe tremendous pride that Ukrainians have in their community and culture. ",
      "index": "00029",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "����� Thank\nyou to our Ukrainian community for helping to make Manitoba the vibrant,\nmulticultural mosaic that we have here and the mosaic that we all love, share\nand appreciate, and really make Manitoba the best province to live all across\nthe country. ",
      "index": "00030",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "����� Thank\nyou, Madam Speaker.� ",
      "index": "00031",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "<b>Mr. Mark </b><b><a name=\"_Toc40905759\">Wasyliw</a></b><b>�(Fort\nGarry):</b> Vyshyvanka Day is an opportunity for Ukrainian �Canadian commu�nities\nand the numerous Ukrainian communities around the world to stand in solidarity\nwith the people of Ukraine. Canada is one of 50 countries around the world in\nwhich Ukrainians take part in International Vyshyvanka Day. ",
      "index": "00032",
      "speaker": "Mark Wasyliw"
    },
    {
      "html": "����� The\nvyshyvanka is a traditional attire for Ukrainian celebrations. It's worn by\npeople regardless of their gender, social status and religious beliefs. The\ntraditional vyshyvanka is a piece of artistic cultural expression. Masterful\nhands embroider colourful patterns and designs specific to the regions of\nUkraine into the traditional white frock.",
      "index": "00033",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "����� With\nthe clothing's increasing popularity in contemporary fashion across the world,\na day has been&nbsp;dedicated to the vyshyvanka to acknowledge the Ukrainian\nheritage these garments represent and promote Ukrainian cultural awareness\nworldwide.",
      "index": "00034",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    { "html": "<b>*</b>\n(13:40)", "index": "00035", "speaker": "" },
    {
      "html": "����� The\nartistry behind a traditional vyshyvanka was inspired by the power of\nprotective symbols. Meanings behind the embroidered symbols and patterns range\nfrom circles that represent the sun and harmony, grape bunches that symbolize\nhappiness and horses that symbolize aspiration.",
      "index": "00036",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "����� Today is an opportunity for Ukrainians, as well as&nbsp;&nbsp;their\ndescendants and supporters, to wear a vyshyvanka and show their Ukrainian\npride. Ukrainians today unite to celebrate their identity, display their\nbeautiful vyshyvanka designs, creating a sense of cultural pride and national\nsolidarity.",
      "index": "00037",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "����� I encourage you all to use this day to learn more and immerse\nyourselves in the Ukrainian history and cultural traditions.",
      "index": "00038",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "����� Thank\nyou, Madam Speaker. ",
      "index": "00039",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "<b>Ms. Cindy\n</b><b><a name=\"_Toc40905760\">Lamoureux</a></b><b>�(Tyndall\nPark):</b> Madam Speaker, I ask for leave to respond to the minister's\nstatement.",
      "index": "00040",
      "speaker": "Cindy Lamoureux"
    },
    {
      "html": "<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> Does the member have leave to respond to the ministerial\nstatement? <i>[Agreed]</i> ",
      "index": "00041",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "<b>Ms.\nLamoureux:</b> It gives me great pleasure to join&nbsp;&nbsp;my colleagues in\nthe Legislature to celebrate Vyshyvanka Day, vyshyvanka being a colourful\ngarment that provides symbols of inspiration, opti�mism and hope for the\nfuture. ",
      "index": "00042",
      "speaker": "Cindy Lamoureux"
    },
    {
      "html": "Madam Speaker, this day is very important to Ukrainians, descendants\nfrom Ukraine and our larger community, and I am exceptionally grateful for the\nstrong presence of Ukrainian heritage here in Manitoba. We are incredibly\nfortunate to have many active community members around us of Ukrainian descent\nwho have made huge contributions to our province in virtually all areas of\nlife, from agriculture to science to health care.",
      "index": "00043",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "I take great pride in our Ukrainian community and our province when\nthinking about the contributions of&nbsp;&nbsp;the community to the labour\nmovement here in&nbsp;&nbsp;Manitoba. As many of my colleagues will know, as\nI've seen them there at events throughout the year, the only surviving labour\nhall associated with the 1919 General Strike is the Ukrainian Labour Temple,\nand it continues to be a great source of pride and a gathering place for the\ncommunity. ",
      "index": "00044",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "I know growing up, Madam Speaker, my parents really instilled in me the\nimportance of community and heritage. My father took me on a trip to Ukraine to\nbetter understand the country as a whole, and for the last seven or eight\nyears, my father and I have continued to host an annual perogy lunch\nspecifically to thank the Ukrainian community. These opportu�nities have\nallowed for me to learn so much and build some amazing relationships within the\ncommunity. ",
      "index": "00045",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "And lastly, Madam Speaker, unfortunately, even in 2020, Ukrainians must\nbe vigilant about their own sovereignty because of ongoing actions from the\nRussia government. We will stand in solidarity with the people from Ukraine\nof�and of Ukraine as they are forced to defend their independence. ",
      "index": "00046",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "����� Thank\nyou, Madam Speaker. ",
      "index": "00047",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "<b>Mr.\nShannon </b><b><a name=\"_Toc40905763\">Martin</a></b><b>�(McPhillips):</b>\nGood afternoon, Madam Speaker. It gives me great pleasure to recognize the\nWayfinders of Seven Oaks School Division. Established in the fall of 2008,\nWayfinders is an after-school mentorship and advocacy program for high-school\nstudents living in poverty or marginalized in northwest Winnipeg. ",
      "index": "00048",
      "speaker": "Shannon Martin"
    },
    {
      "html": "Through a four-pillar model of the additional opportunities and\nsupportive programming outside of&nbsp;&nbsp;the school day�meaning mentorship,\ntutoring, post-secondary and career exploration, service learning\nprogramming�in-school support and advo�cacy, financial support for students and\na bursary program, Wayfinders struggle�or, strives to be a program that fills\nthe gaps and provided additional opportunities for all 425 students it serves.",
      "index": "00049",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "It was created as a program to addresses the gaps and provide the\nadditional supports to students. Through intentional and multi-year\nrelationships that they build with students they serve, Wayfinders works for an\nintervention strategy to create belonging, mastery, independence and generosity\nin students' educational lives. ",
      "index": "00050",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "These strategies are developed in concert with students, their families,\ncaregivers, school personnel and other community-minded individuals to�in a\nwraparound model that students can thrive and succeed in.",
      "index": "00051",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "Wayfinders delivers 25 hours of evening and weekend programming each\nweek, and to date they have supported more than 500 students graduating from\nhigh school and transitioning to post-secondary programming of their choosing. ",
      "index": "00052",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "On October 17th, 2019, Wayfinders celebrated its&nbsp;&nbsp;10th\nanniversary. Held at the program centre at 950 Jefferson Ave., the open house\nwas attended by more then 200 current students, program graduates, families,\ncommunity members and stakeholders. ",
      "index": "00053",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "The event was an opportunity for the official unveiling of the\nstudent-led mural project that acknowledges and celebrates the strength of the\nWayfinders community and students who attend. The&nbsp;&nbsp;mural was created\nas a result of student workshops and was led by local artist Jordan Stranger. ",
      "index": "00054",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "I would like to thank and congratulate the dedicated staff and\nvolunteers of Wayfinders and wish them another helpful and happy 10th�10 years.",
      "index": "00055",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    { "html": "����� Thank\nyou. ", "index": "00056", "speaker": "" },
    {
      "html": "<b>Mr. Jim </b><b><a name=\"_Toc40905765\">Maloway</a></b><b>�(Elmwood):</b>\nLast November 25th, 2019, I raised the issue of door-to-door direct selling\nwith the Minister of Finance (Mr. Fielding). Media reports and complaints from\nmy constituents gave proof to the urgent need for this government to honour\ntheir commitment to help the growing supply of victims of unethical door-to-door\nsales practices. ",
      "index": "00057",
      "speaker": "Jim Maloway"
    },
    {
      "html": "At the time, I highlighted a particular scam perpetrated by Utilebill,\nwhere Manitoba consumers signed contracts promising to pay over $37,000 for a\nfurnace, a HEPA filter, water filter and electronic air cleaner, when all of these\nproducts should've cost less than $10,000, including the equipment and\ninstallation. ",
      "index": "00058",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "����� At the\ntime, the minister offered his deepest sympathy to the victims and he ensured\nthat the House�that his government was taking consumer protection issues\nseriously. I am pleased to see the minister has introduced Bill 38, a bill\namending The Consumer Protection Act, prohibiting the direct sale of furnaces,\nair conditioners, windows and other household systems and supplies. ",
      "index": "00059",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "����� This\nwill bring Manitoba more into line with Ontario and Alberta when it comes to\nbanning this practice. This is a welcome step in the right direction that�to\nprotects consumers going forward. ",
      "index": "00060",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "However, the minister has done absolutely nothing�zero�to compensate\nvictims of these scams. ",
      "index": "00061",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "����� The minister\nis aware that direct sellers in Manitoba are required to be bonded in order to\ncompensate victims. I would like to know: has this government called these\nbonds, and if they have, what&nbsp;&nbsp;day did they call them? Has this been\ndone, and&nbsp;&nbsp;if not, why not? Why is this such a big secret? Is he\ngoing to let these bandits walk off scot-free? ",
      "index": "00062",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "<b>Mr. Jon </b><b><a name=\"_Toc40905767\">Reyes</a></b><b>�(Waverley):</b>\nMadam Speaker, today I&nbsp;have the great pleasure of delivering a private\nmember's statement honouring Waverley constituent�<i>[interjection]</i> ",
      "index": "00063",
      "speaker": "Jon Reyes"
    },
    {
      "html": "<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> Order. ",
      "index": "00064",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "<b>Mr.\nReyes:</b> �and my good friend, Ms. Evangeline Mance. ",
      "index": "00065",
      "speaker": "Jon Reyes"
    },
    {
      "html": "For the past several years, Vangie, as she is known by most, has been\ncommitted to serving her community. As someone who had made the journey to\nimmigrate to Canada, she understands the hardships that many newcomers face.",
      "index": "00066",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "In 2014, Vangie and her late husband, Mario, decided to kick-start the\nLife of Peg Association of Manitoba, a unique platform with a mission to assist\nand guide newcomers as they settle in our province. As a full-time volunteer,\nspending thousands of hours in her organization, she can be found picking newly\nlanded immigrants up from the airport, finding living spaces and directing them\ntowards the right organizations for professional evaluation. ",
      "index": "00067",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "Vangie always keeps her social media open for questions and has even\nprovided her own rental property spaces for families. To help make these\nindividuals feel at home, Vangie also began a sports fest with games of\nvolleyball and badminton. This way, newcomers had the opportunity to play the\nsports they love, meet new friends and network with others, especially others\nwho emigrated from the Philippines.",
      "index": "00068",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "Vangie has been recognized for her outstanding contribution and\ndedication�commitment to her volunteering initiatives. ",
      "index": "00069",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "In January of 2018, she was the recipient of the Pasasalamat, meaning\ngratitude, award for the categories of sports, fitness and immigration\nsettlement.",
      "index": "00070",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "In May 2019, she launched the Mario T. Mance P. Eng Memorial Scholarship\nto continue her husband's legacy. Since its inception, six scholarships have\nbeen awarded for professional engineers from the Philippines who wish to\ncontinue their profession here in Manitoba. ",
      "index": "00071",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "And most recently, Vangie provided a total of 210&nbsp;free meals to front-line\nworkers during this COVID-19 pandemic, just to show some deserved appreciation\nfor their hard work in this difficult time.",
      "index": "00072",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "Madam\nSpeaker, I ask my colleagues to join me in honouring Ms. Evangeline Mance for\nher positive work in the community and for all the lives she has touched\nthrough her love of service. ",
      "index": "00073",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
