      "html": "<b>Mr.\nPallister:</b> Well, I accept that the member has some personal experience in\nhiding from accountability himself, Madam Speaker, but the fact remains that\nthe changes that we have made are in response to a pandemic which is real. The\nmember opposite proposes, as the NDP does quite frequently, that we just borrow\nour way out of it, tax our way out of it and spend our way out of it, and\nthat's why we're in the mess we're in as the most indebted province in the\ncountry. ",
