    {
      "html": "<b>Mr.\nDougald </b><b><a name=\"_Toc40905821\">Lamont</a></b><b>�(St.\nBoniface):</b> I move that under rule 38(1) the ordinary business of the House\nbe set aside to discuss a matter of urgent public importance, namely, the need\nfor urgent attention and debate around the recently announced appointment of\nDavid McLaughlin, campaign manager for the Progressive Conservative Party of\nManitoba in 2016 and 2019, to the role of Clerk of the Executive Council. ",
      "index": "00363",
      "speaker": "Dougald Lamont"
