      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "����� We need to know that the government will be able to treat every\nsingle Manitoban fairly, no matter whether they have a different political\naffiliation from the current government or if they have no political\naffiliation at all. That is what good government does. There is a critical\noverlap in the administration of justice and the administration of public\nservices. Just as justice is blind, so should government deliver services,\naward contracts and support communities based on need and not just the next\nelection cycle. ",
