      "html": "<span lang=\"EN-US\">����� Last year, Madam Speaker, 9,000 people left our\nprovince because of this government's lack of jobs in this province, so I want\nto, you know, tell this government that Manitobans count on them to provide\njobs and they don't want to be, you know, sitting at home. They want\naccountability from, you know, this minister. This minister stood up earlier,\nand I want to quote him. He said: This government will get it right. </span>",
      "index": "00648",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "<span lang=\"EN-US\">����� How can the minister think that cutting 700 jobs\nat Manitoba Hydro is getting it right? Does he not stand up for jobs for\nManitobans? He is a minister in this province, yet he takes direction from a\npremier�fails to stand up for these very workers, these very workers who stood\nin this gallery where they were thanked by this minister and that government\nfor their quick response in a snowstorm, and, I might add, a snowstorm that had\nmore workers from other provinces coming into this province to help. And our\nPublic Utilities Board, you know, they said they'll hold a hearing, but this\ngovernment has the authority to institute that tomorrow. They can do that. </span>",
      "index": "00649",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "<span lang=\"EN-US\">����� They're saying $86 million needs to be saved.\nWell, that was in their election-day promise. Is that coincidence or not? You\nknow, Manitobans deserve to have a job when a job is needed. We're in a COVID‑19\npandemic. How many people are sitting at home not able to pay their job�their rent?\nHow many businesses had to shutter their doors because they can't pay their\nrent because they have no revenue come in?</span>",
      "index": "00650",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "<span lang=\"EN-US\">����� Many of those families are families that had one\nof their partners working at Hydro. Well, guess what? Now neither of them have\nrevenue. And this government thinks that that's the right direction to go?</span>",
      "index": "00651",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "<span lang=\"EN-US\">����� You know, this government is not listening to Manitobans, and\nI want to read a letter to you from a constituent: Dear Bernadette Smith�<i>[interjection]</i>\n</span>",
      "index": "00652",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "<b>Madam Speaker:</b> Order. <span lang=\"EN-US\">Order. </span>",
      "index": "00653",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "<span lang=\"EN-US\">����� Just a couple points there. Even in using your own name, the\nmember should not be using it. Plus, also, if the member's reading from a\nletter, she needs to table three copies of that letter, okay. </span>",
      "index": "00654",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "<b>Mrs.\nSmith:</b> <span lang=\"EN-US\">I'm very upset that the provincial government is\nusing COVID-19 pandemic as an opportunity for public sector cuts, including\nlayoffs at&nbsp;Manitoba Hydro. I am shocked that the Premier (Mr. Pallister)\nis forcing job cuts at Manitoba Hydro. To meet Pallister's demand for cutbacks\nand�<i>[interjection]</i> </span>",
      "index": "00655",
      "speaker": ""
    },
    {
      "html": "<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> Order, please.�� ",
